A Decorator Show House for More Than Show

A new apartment building in the Bronx — the subject of an article on Thursday — was built for families whose primary caregiver has H.I.V. The interiors were designed to be the antithesis of dreary hospital decor, and were decorated in part by editors of Domino, the design magazine.

To what extent does one’s home environment and surroundings play a role in health, especially when a serious illness is a factor?

